      <title>Authenticating with Google Accounts using Microsoft Entra ID</title>
      <link>https://www.sambaiz.net/en/article/544/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 01 Nov 2025 23:47:00 +0900</pubDate>
      <guid>https://www.sambaiz.net/en/article/544/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.microsoft.com/ja-jp/security/business/identity-access/microsoft-entra-id&#34;&gt;Microsoft Entra ID&lt;/a&gt; (formerly Azure Active Directory) is an authentication and authorization platform that, like Amazon Cognito, supports both built-in user management and third-party SAML/OIDC providers.&#xA;While &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.microsoft.com/ja-jp/security/business/microsoft-entra-pricing&#34;&gt;pricing&lt;/a&gt; is charged per user, Azure&amp;rsquo;s EntraID Free can be used at no cost.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Create an &lt;a href=&#34;https://console.cloud.google.com/auth/overview&#34;&gt;OAuth client in Google Cloud&lt;/a&gt; and obtain the Client ID and Secret.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;img_container&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.sambaiz.net/article/544/images/authorized_domains.png&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;img style=&#34;max-width: 100%; width: auto; height: auto;&#34; src=&#34;https://www.sambaiz.net/article/544/images/authorized_domains_hu_23641ea3ef166e5c.png&#34; width=&#34;573&#34; height=&#34;370&#34; alt=&#34;Authorized domains configuration&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The &lt;a href=&#34;https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/entra/external-id/customers/how-to-google-federation-customers&#34;&gt;Authorized URIs&lt;/a&gt; to register with the client include the tenant (directory) ID and domain name xxx.onmicrosoft.com.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
